Official despatches were carried by special messengers (statores), and to tirese the subiect communiales had to furnish hernes, carte, and vessels on demand· Private letters were usually delivered by slaves (tabellarii) of the correspondents, For long distances, especially beyond scas, such service was very expensive, and, except ior the most urgent matters, recourse was had to travellers and tradere going in the desired direction.
